1
00:00:57,634 --> 00:00:58,635
I am...

2
00:00:59,469 --> 00:01:01,221
Alyana Heartily-Ferrer.

3
00:01:01,805 --> 00:01:02,572
I'm your...

4
00:01:02,597 --> 00:01:03,836
guardian angel.

5
00:01:05,266 --> 00:01:07,936
Your target is the hotel owner.

6
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:11,940
Shit!

7
00:01:12,835 --> 00:01:14,757
Arms dealing is Roswell territory.

8
00:01:15,944 --> 00:01:17,003
Boom.

9
00:01:17,028 --> 00:01:19,239
But did I hear that right?
Ma'am Aemie is coming too?

10
00:01:19,823 --> 00:01:20,740
What was it again?

11
00:01:20,740 --> 00:01:22,367
I can't remember anymore.

12
00:01:23,410 --> 00:01:24,953
Why are you asking
Auntie so many questions?

13
00:01:25,328 --> 00:01:26,746
Girl, calm down.

14
00:01:27,122 --> 00:01:28,039
I'm just curious.

15
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:32,335
There's going to be a meeting.

16
00:01:32,961 --> 00:01:34,379
An underground meeting.

17
00:01:35,672 --> 00:01:37,924
You mean we're about
to do something bad?

18
00:01:39,384 --> 00:01:41,010
Why do they all have guns?

19
00:01:52,105 --> 00:01:53,314
But why did all that happen?

20
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:55,727
What is it that you
really want me to know?

21
00:01:58,862 --> 00:01:59,803
That...

22
00:02:05,577 --> 00:02:07,245
That I'm a Mafia boss.

23
00:02:21,676 --> 00:02:22,598
Uh...

24
00:02:27,182 --> 00:02:28,141
Isn't that...

25
00:02:29,309 --> 00:02:31,019
what you're asking me before?

26
00:02:33,646 --> 00:02:35,732
You're just joking, right?

27
00:02:36,024 --> 00:02:37,525
This is just a joke, right?

28
00:02:38,026 --> 00:02:40,236
Because aren't people
in the Mafia bad?

29
00:02:40,236 --> 00:02:41,780
You're not a bad person.

30
00:02:44,699 --> 00:02:45,992
I'm telling the truth.

31
00:02:59,214 --> 00:03:01,508
You mean you're
a bad person, Zeke?

32
00:03:19,901 --> 00:03:20,944
Hey!

33
00:03:20,944 --> 00:03:21,979
Guys!

34
00:03:22,106 --> 00:03:23,900
Help me out here.

35
00:03:25,490 --> 00:03:27,534
Is Dong really a bad person?

36
00:03:30,912 --> 00:03:31,877
Wait.

37
00:03:34,073 --> 00:03:35,455
You guys know it too?

38
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:39,295
You've known all this time?

39
00:03:39,963 --> 00:03:41,214
That Zeke's a Mafia boss?

40
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:57,013
My husband...

41
00:03:57,896 --> 00:03:59,138
is a Mafia boss.

42
00:04:52,827 --> 00:04:54,329
But, Zeke...

43
00:04:55,330 --> 00:04:56,497
What exactly is the Mafia?

44
00:04:56,497 --> 00:04:57,415
Are they...

45
00:04:58,124 --> 00:05:00,418
are they burglars?

46
00:05:00,418 --> 00:05:02,337
Scam syndicates?

47
00:05:02,337 --> 00:05:02,921
People like that?

48
00:05:03,379 --> 00:05:04,464
Are they a cult?

49
00:05:04,464 --> 00:05:06,591
People who steal slippers?

50
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:10,178
Is that why you're rich?

51
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,306
Zeke, seriously.
You could've just borrowed them.

52
00:05:13,306 --> 00:05:15,909
Why did you have
to steal slip—

53
00:05:16,476 --> 00:05:17,769
Ouch!

54
00:05:23,608 --> 00:05:25,818
I'm part of an
underground society.

55
00:05:28,029 --> 00:05:29,614
Sometimes, I steal...

56
00:05:30,615 --> 00:05:32,450
other people's properties.

57
00:05:34,035 --> 00:05:35,161
I pull down

58
00:05:35,161 --> 00:05:36,955
every underground business

59
00:05:37,372 --> 00:05:38,957
that poses a threat to us.

60
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:43,586
I hunt down those who try
to compete with my work.

61
00:05:47,090 --> 00:05:48,007
Hunt down?

62
00:05:52,971 --> 00:05:55,473
So you kill innocent people?

63
00:06:00,019 --> 00:06:01,034
No.

64
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:04,378
I mean...

65
00:06:09,809 --> 00:06:11,436
if I need to.

66
00:06:32,802 --> 00:06:34,762
So that means you're
a bad person, Zeke?

67
00:06:40,518 --> 00:06:41,102
Huh?

68
00:06:44,856 --> 00:06:46,441
Have you killed a lot of people?

69
00:06:54,991 --> 00:06:55,825
Yes.

70
00:07:06,544 --> 00:07:08,421
It all started when I was eight.

71
00:07:09,964 --> 00:07:11,466
After Mom's death.

72
00:07:14,594 --> 00:07:16,471
My dad started to train me.

73
00:07:17,972 --> 00:07:20,308
He taught me all the things
I needed to know.

74
00:07:21,142 --> 00:07:22,560
About business,

75
00:07:23,019 --> 00:07:24,270
and in the mafia.

76
00:07:25,021 --> 00:07:26,189
Every morning...

77
00:07:28,566 --> 00:07:30,026
I would wake up in pain.

78
00:07:31,069 --> 00:07:34,030
My body was full of cuts
and bruises from training.

79
00:07:41,012 --> 00:07:42,055
Uhh, Dad.

80
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:44,457
Kaizer's inviting me
to go to Jerson's house.

81
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:48,461
He has this new video game.

82
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:50,880
Wallace is there too.

83
00:07:51,881 --> 00:07:54,175
No, you don't have time
for such an immature play.

84
00:07:54,509 --> 00:07:57,637
Get back in your room
and prepare for training.

85
00:07:58,179 --> 00:07:59,472
You need to be strong,

86
00:07:59,889 --> 00:08:00,765
to avenge your mother.

87
00:08:00,765 --> 00:08:02,850
Remember, you still
have a lot to learn.

88
00:08:03,351 --> 00:08:04,268
<i>But still,</i>

89
00:08:05,311 --> 00:08:06,354
<i>I needed to learn.</i>

90
00:08:06,771 --> 00:08:08,981
<i>I needed to learn
how to be numb.</i>

91
00:08:22,161 --> 00:08:23,871
Is that all you got, son?

92
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:27,291
Are you going to
end up like the rest?

93
00:08:29,585 --> 00:08:30,588
Weak?

94
00:08:30,795 --> 00:08:31,796
Pathetic?

95
00:08:59,198 --> 00:09:00,366
<i>At the age of 10,</i>

96
00:09:03,369 --> 00:09:04,912
I learned how to pull...

97
00:09:07,123 --> 00:09:09,208
the trigger without mercy.

98
00:09:18,384 --> 00:09:19,110
What?

99
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:20,247
Are you a coward?

100
00:09:21,220 --> 00:09:23,139
Everyone around you
will die like your mother

101
00:09:23,139 --> 00:09:25,016
if you stay spineless like that!

102
00:09:26,309 --> 00:09:27,232
Kill him!

103
00:09:37,111 --> 00:09:38,029
But Dad...

104
00:09:39,906 --> 00:09:40,865
I said!

105
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:43,618
Kill him!

106
00:09:45,953 --> 00:09:46,454
Sir!

107
00:09:46,454 --> 00:09:47,513
Please don't, sir!

108
00:09:47,538 --> 00:09:48,407
Have mercy, sir!

109
00:09:49,165 --> 00:09:50,180
Please don't!

110
00:09:58,466 --> 00:10:00,593
<i>That's when I started
to become a killer.</i>

111
00:10:01,677 --> 00:10:03,888
<i>That's when I started
to become...</i>

112
00:10:03,888 --> 00:10:04,805
Evil.

113
00:10:10,102 --> 00:10:11,812
That was the birth
of the new me.

114
00:10:14,232 --> 00:10:16,150
Merciless and cold-hearted.

115
00:10:21,656 --> 00:10:24,992
I endured every curse and
humiliation my father threw at me.

116
00:10:31,165 --> 00:10:34,835
He blamed me for Mom's death
because I couldn't protect her.

117
00:10:39,131 --> 00:10:41,759
What could an eight-year-old
possibly have done?

118
00:10:43,678 --> 00:10:46,389
The man is a damn sick moron.

119
00:10:47,598 --> 00:10:49,100
My training wasn't fun.

120
00:10:50,351 --> 00:10:51,811
It was survival.

121
00:10:52,937 --> 00:10:54,063
It felt like...

122
00:10:54,814 --> 00:10:58,734
I was playing hide-and-seek
with death every single day.

123
00:11:01,862 --> 00:11:03,239
Not by choice.

124
00:11:05,950 --> 00:11:06,951
But because...

125
00:11:08,286 --> 00:11:10,288
I needed to learn the skills,

126
00:11:11,330 --> 00:11:12,331
to hunt down...

127
00:11:13,457 --> 00:11:15,584
the bastards who
murdered my mother.

128
00:11:16,168 --> 00:11:17,169
I've never...

129
00:11:17,878 --> 00:11:20,548
felt real love or care
since my mom died.

130
00:11:21,090 --> 00:11:22,508
And I stopped believing...

131
00:11:24,176 --> 00:11:26,762
that I'll ever feel
those things again.

132
00:11:44,405 --> 00:11:47,950
I know a lot of terrible things
happened in your past, Zeke.

133
00:11:51,370 --> 00:11:53,789
But you don't have
to keep living there.

134
00:11:56,876 --> 00:11:59,170
And I'm sure that's what
your mom would've wanted too.

135
00:12:02,715 --> 00:12:04,175
What do you mean?

136
00:12:10,598 --> 00:12:12,016
I'm here for you.

137
00:12:14,894 --> 00:12:16,562
I'll never leave you.

138
00:12:19,148 --> 00:12:20,483
You don't hate me?

139
00:12:22,693 --> 00:12:23,861
For who I am?

140
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:26,947
And for the things I've done?

141
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,293
I'll be honest with you, okay?

142
00:12:43,381 --> 00:12:45,841
When you told me
you were a Mafia boss,

143
00:12:47,551 --> 00:12:49,345
I got really scared.

144
00:12:54,266 --> 00:12:55,893
But after you told
me everything...

145
00:12:57,686 --> 00:13:00,773
I realized you're not
really a bad person, Zeke.

146
00:13:03,567 --> 00:13:04,902
Because...

147
00:13:06,695 --> 00:13:10,032
the Zeke I got to know
was never a bad person.

148
00:13:17,081 --> 00:13:18,499
I love you, Zeke.

149
00:13:21,001 --> 00:13:24,171
Even if you were the
most evil person in the world.

150
00:13:26,257 --> 00:13:28,592
Can you say that
again for me, please?

151
00:13:30,553 --> 00:13:32,509
Are you deaf or something, Zeke?

152
00:13:32,763 --> 00:13:35,182
Come on! I said...

153
00:13:39,478 --> 00:13:40,646
<i>"Mahal kita."</i>

154
00:13:43,482 --> 00:13:45,484
In English.

155
00:13:45,901 --> 00:13:46,819
I...

156
00:13:47,611 --> 00:13:48,904
love—

157
00:14:03,002 --> 00:14:04,837
I love you even more, wife.

158
00:14:34,319 --> 00:14:35,129
Huh!

159
00:14:35,330 --> 00:14:37,082
Why did he laugh?

160
00:14:38,496 --> 00:14:39,997
Did I do something wrong?

161
00:14:41,207 --> 00:14:44,627
Hey, maybe I should ask
someone to teach me how to kiss!

162
00:14:46,045 --> 00:14:47,129
Maybe Kaizer?

163
00:14:47,671 --> 00:14:48,394
No?

164
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:10,796
Oops! Porn!

165
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:13,090
- What the fuck?!
- Shit! Not you, boss!

166
00:16:13,115 --> 00:16:15,284
- Mr. Roswell, wait! Don't!
- Don't!

167
00:16:17,052 --> 00:16:18,762
A lot of women would be left mourning.

168
00:16:19,263 --> 00:16:20,514
No, wait!

169
00:16:21,891 --> 00:16:22,547
Aemie!

170
00:16:23,225 --> 00:16:26,312
Oh, right. Right,
don't kill Kaizer, Zeke.

171
00:16:26,604 --> 00:16:27,500
Don't.

172
00:16:27,646 --> 00:16:28,897
- Mmm.
- Don't.

173
00:16:29,189 --> 00:16:32,151
Give me one goddamn
reason and I'll spare his life.

174
00:16:32,610 --> 00:16:33,277
Oh no!

175
00:16:33,277 --> 00:16:33,961
Hey!

176
00:16:33,986 --> 00:16:34,795
Uh...

177
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:36,363
Oh no! Is there a call-a-friend?

178
00:16:36,739 --> 00:16:38,449
Hey! Wait! Wait!

179
00:16:38,449 --> 00:16:40,200
This is so hard, let
me think first. Wait!

180
00:16:40,534 --> 00:16:41,535
Uhm...

181
00:16:41,785 --> 00:16:42,995
Oh no, I can't
think of anything.

182
00:16:42,995 --> 00:16:43,579
Wait!

183
00:16:43,662 --> 00:16:45,247
- Wait. Uhm...
- Aemie, hurry!

184
00:16:46,457 --> 00:16:48,667
Oh! I got it! I got it!

185
00:16:51,337 --> 00:16:52,437
Because...

186
00:16:52,588 --> 00:16:54,965
I still need Kaizer to
teach me how to kiss.

187
00:16:55,215 --> 00:16:56,125
Huh?

188
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:02,593
Boss, wait.

189
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,656
Mr. Roswell.

190
00:17:03,932 --> 00:17:04,914
Mr. Roswell.

191
00:17:06,644 --> 00:17:07,656
Mr. Roswell.

192
00:17:09,355 --> 00:17:11,565
Fine, Zeke. Just kill Kaizer.

193
00:17:11,565 --> 00:17:12,562
Oh, crap.

194
00:17:55,734 --> 00:17:56,944
That's her husband?

195
00:17:57,194 --> 00:17:59,113
Aemie is so lucky.

196
00:17:59,279 --> 00:18:00,239
Where have you been, Grace?

197
00:18:00,239 --> 00:18:02,700
We've been neighbors for a while,
yet you're still behind on the gossip.

198
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:06,412
Aren't you heading home yet?

199
00:18:06,745 --> 00:18:07,703
It's getting late.

200
00:18:08,122 --> 00:18:09,181
Have you eaten yet?

201
00:18:09,206 --> 00:18:10,624
Not yet, Amesyl.

202
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:11,850
Alright.

203
00:18:11,875 --> 00:18:12,710
Go home.

204
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:13,877
Eat at your house.

205
00:18:14,420 --> 00:18:15,546
Alright, Amesyl.

206
00:18:15,546 --> 00:18:16,839
I'll get going first.

207
00:18:17,089 --> 00:18:17,798
Yeah.

208
00:18:24,096 --> 00:18:25,556
Are you sure about that?

209
00:18:26,807 --> 00:18:27,615
Yes.

210
00:18:28,434 --> 00:18:29,302
Don't worry.

211
00:18:30,102 --> 00:18:31,145
I'll deal with it.

212
00:18:31,478 --> 00:18:32,513
See you then.

213
00:18:41,155 --> 00:18:42,119
Auntie?

214
00:18:44,658 --> 00:18:46,326
Oh, why are you still awake?

215
00:18:48,579 --> 00:18:49,767
It's still early.

216
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:51,248
Where have you been, Auntie?

217
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:53,792
I just went somewhere.

218
00:18:53,792 --> 00:18:54,376
Why?

219
00:18:56,378 --> 00:18:57,671
Is something wrong, Auntie?

220
00:18:57,963 --> 00:18:59,256
Who were you talking to earlier?

221
00:18:59,923 --> 00:19:01,425
You were even speaking English.

222
00:19:02,801 --> 00:19:03,846
Huh?

223
00:19:05,053 --> 00:19:06,260
Forget about that.

224
00:19:08,348 --> 00:19:08,974
Oh.

225
00:19:08,974 --> 00:19:09,893
No.

226
00:19:10,851 --> 00:19:14,208
I was just practicing my favorite
lines from the movie I watched earlier.

227
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:16,194
You know, those
Hollywood movies.

228
00:19:17,357 --> 00:19:18,315
Wait.

229
00:19:18,358 --> 00:19:19,253
Niece.

230
00:19:19,985 --> 00:19:21,086
It's getting late.

231
00:19:21,111 --> 00:19:22,237
Why aren't you asleep yet?

232
00:19:22,237 --> 00:19:23,947
You have an early
class tomorrow.

233
00:19:26,366 --> 00:19:27,259
Alright.

234
00:19:27,284 --> 00:19:28,096
Good night.

235
00:19:33,165 --> 00:19:35,417
Those two really are
mother and daughter.

236
00:19:43,842 --> 00:19:46,929
Should I tell cuz
about our adventure?

237
00:19:48,597 --> 00:19:50,557
She might get jealous, you know?

238
00:19:50,891 --> 00:19:52,643
It was like we were
in an action movie.

239
00:19:52,643 --> 00:19:54,394
There were so many...

240
00:19:54,978 --> 00:19:56,538
Bang, bang, bang.

241
00:19:56,563 --> 00:19:57,397
And those guys.

242
00:19:57,397 --> 00:19:59,316
Those really tall guys.

243
00:20:07,991 --> 00:20:08,951
I love you.

244
00:20:12,371 --> 00:20:14,832
Hey, where'd you get that, Dong?

245
00:20:15,916 --> 00:20:16,834
Does it matter?

246
00:20:18,961 --> 00:20:19,378
Of course.

247
00:20:20,254 --> 00:20:22,339
Everything that
occupies space is matter.

248
00:20:24,508 --> 00:20:26,635
Can't you just say,
"I love you too"?

249
00:20:29,596 --> 00:20:30,722
I love you too.

250
00:20:37,229 --> 00:20:38,021
But...

251
00:20:39,022 --> 00:20:39,982
Come on, Dong.

252
00:20:39,982 --> 00:20:43,151
You know my favorite
color is pink, right?

253
00:20:44,319 --> 00:20:45,779
Red is the color of love.

254
00:20:46,113 --> 00:20:48,198
But pink is the color of me.

255
00:20:48,490 --> 00:20:50,325
Myself and I.

256
00:20:58,250 --> 00:20:59,084
Where's your ring?

257
00:21:02,421 --> 00:21:03,714
This is not it.

258
00:21:04,798 --> 00:21:06,341
This one's very plain looking.

259
00:21:10,971 --> 00:21:12,014
Let me get that.

260
00:21:14,725 --> 00:21:15,767
Hey!

261
00:21:16,643 --> 00:21:18,812
You're the one who took my ring?

262
00:21:19,062 --> 00:21:19,813
No.

263
00:21:19,813 --> 00:21:21,190
Why would I take it?

264
00:21:21,648 --> 00:21:22,691
I bought a new one.

265
00:21:23,108 --> 00:21:23,984
No way!

266
00:21:24,192 --> 00:21:25,085
Seriously?!

267
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:26,069
Seriously.

268
00:21:28,196 --> 00:21:29,573
You're the one who stole it.

269
00:21:31,199 --> 00:21:32,951
You weren't taking care of it.

270
00:21:33,076 --> 00:21:33,452
Seriously!

271
00:21:33,452 --> 00:21:36,163
Do you know how worried I
was when it went missing?

272
00:21:36,330 --> 00:21:37,998
And then you just took it—

273
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:24,670
I'm almost done.

274
00:22:27,172 --> 00:22:28,090
As of today,

275
00:22:29,049 --> 00:22:31,468
only one of those
bastards is still alive.

276
00:22:33,011 --> 00:22:34,930
Is this about your mom, Zeke?

277
00:22:36,556 --> 00:22:37,849
The others are dead?

278
00:22:41,478 --> 00:22:42,145
I mean,

279
00:22:43,522 --> 00:22:45,399
I was almost done
with my dreams.

280
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:48,568
But you arrived

281
00:22:48,568 --> 00:22:49,820
and gave me another.

282
